ou!',100,NULL,'Meet in Next House (W71), Lobby','2010-04-09 00:00:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(148,'FIREHOSE: Origami Construction, Inc.','OC Inc. is a supplier of creations involving structural business cards and a complete lack of glue. We work pre-frosh for long hours on fiendish projects. Come hang out, eat our food, and take classes until stupid late. ',100,NULL,'6th floor of Building 24','2010-04-09 00:00:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic,class,student, oraganization'),(149,'Sweet Rave Party','RAVE!!! RAVE RAVE RAVE (glow sticks!) RAVE RAVE RAVE. (Dance the night away.)',100,NULL,'Random Hall (NW61)','2010-04-09 00:17:00',60,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(150,'FIREHOSE: The Art of Explication','Come discuss some of the most beautiful passages in the literary world using techniques and literary devices. This will be a nice discussion of central literature themes. Come hang out, eat our food, and take classes until stupid late. ',100,NULL,'6th floor of Building 24','2010-04-09 01:00:00',60,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic,class,student, oraganization'),(151,'Hot Dogs and Game Night ','Wonder what we call the instant heart attack? Come try some!!! Or if not, just join us for rockband, super smash bros, DJ Hero, jenga, mafia and hoopla; we wonÃ•t force you to clog your arteries.',100,NULL,'New House (W70), House 2','2010-04-09 01:00:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(152,'FIREHOSE: Generating Function','Learn about the basic properties of generating functions and a few of their applications in combinatorics. Finish with a powerful method for evaluating summations. This class is part of ESP\'s FIREHOSE events. Come hang out, eat our food, and take classes until stupid late. ',100,NULL,'6th floor of building 24','2010-04-09 01:00:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic,class,student, oraganization'),(153,'FIREHOSE: Maxwell\'s Equations','From observations of charge and special relativity, we will derive the four Maxwell\'s equations. IT\'LL BE AWESOME. This class is part of ESP\'s FIREHOSE Event! Come hang out, eat our food, and take classes until stupid late. ',100,NULL,'6th floor of Building 24','2010-04-09 01:00:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic,class,student, oraganization'),(154,'FIREHOSE: Card Games','Learn to be a socialite while showing off your mental prowess through poker, rummy, trump, solitaire, Marjolet (what the heck?) and any other card games you can think of. Hang out, eat our food, and take classes until stupid late. ',100,NULL,'6th floor of building 24','2010-04-09 01:00:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic,class,student, oraganization'),(155,'Movie Night','Join us for a night of movies and enjoy some snacks and refreshments.',100,NULL,'Ashdown House (NW35)','2010-04-09 01:00:00',180,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(156,'Zombie Movie Marathon','BRAAAAAAAAAINS!!! Come help us fight off wave after wave of the infected. Or just eat some popcorn and laugh.',100,NULL,'Burton-Conner House (W51), TV Lounge','2010-04-09 01:00:00',300,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(157,'Infinite Crepes!','This is what happens when you take the limit of one square crepe divided by zero crepes!',100,NULL,'Alpha Delta Phi, 351 Massachusetts Ave., Cambridge','2010-04-09 02:00:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','fraternity, sorority, living'),(158,'Vermonster Challenge ','Imagine all the ice cream you could ever eat, smothered in oreos, M&amp;Ms, sprinkles and more. That is a vermonster, and we need your help to defeat it. ',100,NULL,'Sigma Phi Epsilon (w/ the big red door), 518 Beacon St., Boston','2010-04-09 03:00:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','fraternity, sorority, living'),(159,'Sleepers Anonymous','Sleep is an addiction. The first step towards overcoming your addiction is admitting you have a problem. Sleepers Anonymous is a support group formed to help people like you overcome this addiction. Come, and we will all fight it together.',100,NULL,'Random Hall (NW61)','2010-04-09 03:17:00',60,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(160,'Breakfast!!!','Come start your CPW with a hearty breakfast and mingle with McCormick ladies and other prefrosh before the Chancellor\'s Welcome!!! ',100,NULL,'McCormick Hall (W4), Country Kitchen','2010-04-09 07:00:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(161,'Read The Tech!','Friday\'s issue of The Tech comes out today, and we have it on good authority that it\'ll be quite an issue. See for yourself at any of our distribution points all across campus, or online at http://tech.mit.edu.',100,NULL,'All over campus!','2010-04-09 08:00:00',-21180240,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','arts,student, oraganization'),(162,'Department of Earth, Atmospheric and Planetary Sciences (EAPS) Open House/Continental Breakfast','The current opportunities in the earth sciences, meteorology and ocean sciences as well as planetary sciences and astronomy are numerous, with challenging and rewarding jobs awaiting graduates. Please join the EAPS Department faculty for an informal discussion of the options within our academic program.',100,NULL,'Room 54-923','2010-04-09 08:00:00',60,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic,parents'),(163,'Breakfast of Champions','Today is going to be a long day full of fun events, so why not refuel with a delicious and hearty &quot;Breakfast of Champions&quot;, complete with a scrumptious assortment of yummy bagels, cereal, fresh fruit, yogurt, and juices!',100,NULL,'Simmons Hall (W79)','2010-04-09 08:00:00',90,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(164,'Bacon and Egg Breakfast','It\'s BAAACON!!! Bacon Bacon Bacon BAAACON!!! and eggs... and toast and stuff too... but seriously... BAAACON!!!!',100,NULL,'Burton-Conner House (W51), TV Lounge','2010-04-09 08:00:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(165,'Breakfast','Come enjoy all shapes, sizes and flavors of pancakes as well as waffles and smoothies.',100,NULL,'New House (W70), Arcade','2010-04-09 08:00:00',840,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(166,'More Breakfast than YOUR BODY HAS ROOM FOR!!!','It\'s the return of the OM NOM NOMELETTE! And this time, it has an army of OVER 9000 PANCAKES!',100,NULL,'Random Hall (NW61)','2010-04-09 08:17:00',60,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(167,'Breakfast with the Skulls','Breakfast is the most important meal of the day. Drop by Skullhouse and enjoy a morning meal of omeletes made to order, pancakes as big as your head, and other morning delights.',100,NULL,'Phi Kappa Sigma, 530 Beacon St., Boston','2010-04-09 08:30:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','fraternity, sorority, living'),(168,'Morning Coffee with Faculty and Staff','Prefrosh, parents and families, please join MIT faculty and staff for an informal chat and a cup of coffee to start your day! Drop in anytime during this hour, which precedes the Chancellor\'s Welcome and Featured Faculty Speakers.',100,NULL,'Kresge Auditorium (W16), Lobby ','2010-04-09 09:00:00',60,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','featured,parents'),(169,'Building Weatherization Workshop','Learn and apply cost-effective means of making existing buildings more energy-efficient. This workshop consists of an overview of building weatherization by MIT Facilities followed by application of demonstrated techniques at various locations in E52. Limited to 20 participants.',100,NULL,'Room E52-460','2010-04-09 09:00:00',180,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','student, oraganization'),(170,'UROP Tours Sign-up','See first-hand the accessible and cutting edge research opportunities available to MIT undergraduates! A complete list of tour descriptions will be available at registration. Tour sign-up required to participate. <strong>Note: Sign up begins on Thursday and may not extend to Friday due to limited availability.</strong> Limit one tour per student.  For general information about the UROP program, come to the UROP discussion panel Friday, April 9th at 12pm in Kresge Auditorium (W16).',100,NULL,'Sign up in the Student Center (W20), 2nd Floor, La Sala de Puerto Rico','2010-04-09 09:00:00',180,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','featured'),(171,'Financial Aid Appointments','For questions regarding aid, loans, student employment, and/or billing, please visit the Student Financial Services (SFS) desk in La Sala de Puerto Rico. General questions are answered immediately or you will be advised to schedule a 20-minute appointment. Scheduled appointments are limited and held in 11-120.',100,NULL,'Sign up in the Student Center (W20), 2nd Floor, La Sala de Puerto Rico','2010-04-09 09:00:00',480,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','featured,parents'),(172,'Parent Hospitality Lounge','Grab a cup of coffee or tea and chat with current MIT parents as well as other parents of MIT prefrosh. Also, learn about the MIT Parents Association and the Parent Connector Network from current volunteers and staff.',100,NULL,'Student Center (W20), 2nd Floor, La Sala de Puerto Rico','2010-04-09 09:00:00',480,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','featured,parents'),(173,'Hillel Open House','Stop by at any time to the Hillel Office (basement of W11) to meet the Hillel Staff. While you\'re here, you can buy your very own MIT Hillel t-shirt (in Hebrew).',100,NULL,'Religious Activities Center (W11), Basement','2010-04-09 09:00:00',480,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','religious,student, oraganization'),(174,'Classes','Many MIT classes open their doors to prefrosh during CPW. See your registration packet for the list sorted by date, time and subject. Before sitting in on a class that is not on the list, you <strong>must</strong> receive permission from the department in advance; some classes will be holding exams or do not have space to accommodate visitors.',100,NULL,'Various Locations','2010-04-09 09:00:00',480,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','class'),(175,'CPW Registration and Help Desk','<br>',100,NULL,'Student Center (W20), 2nd Floor, La Sala de Puerto Rico','2010-04-09 09:00:00',660,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','featured,parents'),(176,'Breakfast at DKE!','Just woke up and hungry? Have a love of breakfast food? Come get some hot breakfast made to order by our chef Tom.  Pancakes, sausage, bacon, omelets - the choice is yours.',100,NULL,'Delta Kappa Epsilon, 403 Memorial Dr., Cambridge','2010-04-09 09:30:00',90,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','fraternity, sorority, living'),(177,'Breakfast at Next: All-you-can-eat Pancakes!','Eat breakfast at Next House and learn more about MIT dorm life! The main event is pancakes, but we\'ll also have fresh fruit, juice, and more tasty breakfast treats. Come enjoy our free food!',100,NULL,'Next House (W71), Dining','2010-04-09 09:30:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(178,'Continental Breakfast','It may not be Holiday Inn, but, hey, it\'s free.',100,NULL,'Theta Delta Chi, 372 Memorial Dr., Cambridge','2010-04-09 10:00:00',60,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','fraternity, sorority, living'),(179,'Chancellor\'s Welcome &amp; Featured Faculty Speakers','Chancellor Phillip Clay welcomes you to CPW and introduces the featured MIT faculty speakers: Dr. Nancy Kanwisher (SB \'80, PhD \'86), Department of Brain &amp; Cognitive Sciences, whose research is on the cutting edge of cognitive function and development (http://bcs.mit.edu/people/kanwisher.html); and Dr. Jonathan Gruber (SB \'87), Department of Economics, a renowned expert in public finance and health and advised both the Clinton and Obama administrations (http://econ-www.mit.edu/faculty/gruberj/shortbio).',100,NULL,'Kresge Auditorium (W16)','2010-04-09 10:00:00',90,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','featured,academic,parents'),(180,'MacGregor House Tours','Come and check out our dorm. Our friendly and informative tour guides will show you around our entries and give you some insight into our house and culture.',100,NULL,'MacGregor House (W61)','2010-04-09 10:00:00',300,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory,parents'),(181,'McCormick Dorm Tours','Wondering why guys at MIT are jealous of girls at McCormick? Come see the rooms, courtyard, and the famed penthouses. Tours will run every 20-30 minutes. ',100,NULL,'McCormick Hall (W4), Lobby','2010-04-09 10:00:00',360,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(182,'Toilet Paper Dodgeball','Come to CPW! Meet new and exciting people! Hit them with rolls of toilet paper!',100,NULL,'Random Hall (NW61)','2010-04-09 10:47:00',60,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','dormitory'),(183,'Dept. of Architecture Open House','Join faculty, staff and students for a short presentation and tour of our facilities. Architecture majors are taught to be the creators, designers, builders, collaborators and visionaries of the environments of the future. Our curriculum includes architecture design, building technology, visual studies, design computation, and the history and theory of architecture and art.',100,NULL,'Room 7-431','2010-04-09 11:00:00',90,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic,parents'),(184,'Speed Bridge Building','What fun is a bridge if you can\'t build it in under 5 minutes? Come hang out with the MIT Steel Bridge Team as we build our 20 foot long, 1250lb -carrying bridge faster than... well, come find out!',100,NULL,'Student Center Steps (W20)','2010-04-09 11:00:00',180,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic,parents,student, oraganization'),(185,'How to Help Your Daughter: Sororities at MIT Information Session','At MIT, sororities serve as a wonderful resource for academic, leadership, and personal support. Come meet women from MIT\'s sororities and find out how your daughter can become a part of the largest women\'s community on campus.',100,NULL,'Student Center (W20), 3rd Floor, Twenty Chimneys','2010-04-09 11:30:00',60,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','fraternity, sorority, living,parents'),(186,'CSAIL: A peek inside the lab','Work at the Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence Laboratory spans a vast range of exciting projects, from fitting a thousand cores on a single chip to robotic gardens, early seizure detection, and even computer algorithms based on the ancient art of origami. Join us for a peek inside the lab!',100,NULL,'Room 32-G449 (Kiva conference room)','2010-04-09 11:30:00',90,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic,parents'),(187,'MIT Medical Open House','Drop in at the Medical Department to learn more about the wide variety of health services available on campus as well as MIT student insurance coverage. Clinical staff, senior administrators and students will be on hand to answer any questions.',100,NULL,'MIT Medical (E23), Lobby','2010-04-09 11:30:00',90,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','featured,parents'),(188,'Brain and Cognitive Sciences Open House','Come learn about Course 9, Brain and Cognitive Sciences, during this Open House and Lab Tour session.',100,NULL,'Building 46, 3rd Floor Atrium','2010-04-09 11:30:00',90,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic'),(189,'Women\'s Leadership Brunch: Perspectives of Undergraduate Women Leaders @ MIT','Join us for brunch and meet some amazing young women. Be inspired by stories of their MIT experience, hear how they became leaders in our community, and get useful advice for success in college. The first 50 admitted women to attend will receive a special gift!',100,NULL,'Student Center (W20), 3rd Floor, Mezzanine Lounge','2010-04-09 11:30:00',90,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','featured'),(190,'BCS Lab Tours','Meet current undergraduates in MIT\'s Brain &amp; Cognitive Sciences Department for a personal tour of cutting-edge neuroscience and cognitive science research laboratories.  Lunch provided.',100,NULL,'Building 46, 3rd floor atrium','2010-04-09 11:30:00',90,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','academic,parents,student, oraganization'),(191,'Career Development Center Open House','How do you... find a summer internship or a job after graduation? write a resume? apply to graduate school? Come talk with staff about the wide variety of services and support we offer students. Also learn about the F/ASIP program for Freshmen!',100,NULL,'Room 12-170','2010-04-09 11:30:00',120,NULL,NULL,37,'confirmed','featured,academic,parents'),(192,'Global Education Office Open House',